  \begin {tikzcd}
    C\ar [rr, bend left, "L"] & \bot  & D\ar [ll, bend left, "R"]
    & 1_C\ar [r, "\eta "] & RL & LR\ar [r, "\epsilon "] & 1_D\makebox [0pt][l]\,
  \end {tikzcd}



 be an adjunction. Then the composite
RL is a monad on C, with unit \eta  and counit R\epsilon  L, the latter defined by whiskering.

Since universal elements are initial, the colimit
  D\xrightarrow {\lambda } \operatorname *{colim} D of a diagram J\xrightarrow {D} C is
  initial in the category of elements \text {el}(\operatorname *{Cocone}_D),
  in the sense that for any other cocone
  D\xrightarrow {\mu } c, there exists a unique map \operatorname *{lim} D\to  c so that each of
  the following triangles commute:




